      "comment": "OUR RUPEE (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Ballarat behind Edie Monsoon (22.82) in a T3 Grade 7. Has the pace to be prominent. Expected to feature in the finish again. MISS HOOVER (8) finds it hard to win but looks close to breaking through. Has been in the minors the last two runs, the latest finishing second (24.62) at this track. Expected to be in the finish again. MORNING DAWN (3) has mixed form a little and missed the frame the last two but was a Maiden winner three back (22.65) at Shepparton over 390m. Well placed here and can atone this time. NULLA DANNY BOY (4) has claims if he runs up to his best.",
